# Documentation Branding Standards

## Signal Amber Brand Requirements

ALL documentation in Agentic repositories MUST follow the Signal Amber design system.

### Reference Document

See `docs/src/styles/custom.css` for the live implementation of the Signal Amber theme.

### Color Palette (Signal Amber)

| Purpose | Hex |
|---------|-----|
| Background | `#0C0A09` (warm stone) |
| Surface/Cards | `#1C1917` |
| Primary (Amber) | `#F59E0B` |
| Secondary (Amber Light) | `#FCD34D` |
| Text Primary | `#FAFAF9` |
| Text Secondary | `#A8A29E` |
| Success | `#10b981` |
| Warning | `#f59e0b` |
| Error | `#ef4444` |

### Typography

| Element | Font | Weight |
|---------|------|--------|
| Headings | Instrument Sans | 600-700 |
| Body | Inter | 400-500 |
| Code | JetBrains Mono | 400 |

## Documentation Checklist

Before pushing documentation changes:

- [ ] Uses Signal Amber color palette (warm stone backgrounds)
- [ ] Headings use Instrument Sans font
- [ ] Body text uses Inter font
- [ ] Code blocks use JetBrains Mono
- [ ] Links are amber (`#F59E0B`)
- [ ] Code blocks have proper contrast
- [ ] Admonitions follow semantic colors
- [ ] Focus states are visible (accessibility)
- [ ] Meets WCAG AA contrast requirements

## Do NOT

- Do not use the old cyan/dark theme (`#06b6d4`, `#0a0f1a`, Space Grotesk)
- Do not use light theme as default
- Do not use different primary colors
- Do not use non-standard fonts without approval
- Do not create custom color schemes per-repo
- Do not ignore accessibility requirements

## Do

- Use Signal Amber theme consistently
- Use warm stone backgrounds (`#0C0A09`)
- Use Instrument Sans for headings
- Use Inter for body text
- Use JetBrains Mono for code
- Apply the Signal Amber CSS for your doc tool
- Follow the type scale specification
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Test with reduced motion preference
